#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:632
msgid "Welcome to Plover Theme!"
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:633
msgid "Welcome to the Plover Theme! This article provides a comprehensive overview of its powerful features, giving you everything you need to start building your dream WordPress site."
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:637
msgid "What is Full Site Editing (FSE)?"
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:638
msgid "This article introduces Full Site Editing (FSE) in plain language, compares it to classic theming, and explains core concepts like blocks, templates, and global styles to help you start building with the Plover Theme."
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:642
msgid "Site Editor Overview"
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:643
msgid "Welcome to the Site Editor—the heart of Full Site Editing in WordPress. This article walks you through each part of the interface, explains what everything does, and helps you feel confident designing your entire site with Plover Theme."
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:647
msgid "Navigation sidebar"
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:648
msgid "This article introduces the Navigation Sidebar, your command center in the WordPress Site Editor. Learn to use it to preview content, manage styles, templates, and patterns, and create new templates for your Plover site."
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:652
msgid "Site Editor Area"
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:653
msgid "This article walks you through the WordPress Site Editor interface. Master the Styles sidebar — where you can customize global styles, individual blocks, and even add custom CSS for your Plover site."
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:659
msgid "Dark Mode Tutorials"
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:662
msgid "Dark Mode Quick Start"
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:663
msgid "This quick start guide shows you how to enable dark mode in Plover Theme. You'll learn to add the toggle button using a preset pattern and preview dark mode directly in the Site Editor."
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:667
msgid "Block Level Dark Mode"
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:668
msgid "This article explains block-level dark mode in Plover Theme. Learn how to force specific container blocks—like Group, Row, and Columns — to always stay in dark or light mode, independent of your global settings."
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:672
msgid "Fine-tuning Dark Mode Colors"
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:673
msgid "Discover how to fine-tune dark mode colors in Plover Theme. Learn the exact color inversion rules for light and dark modes, and explore how to manage and customize the color palette directly in the Site Editor."
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:677
msgid "Show or hide blocks based on color mode"
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:678
msgid "Learn to control block visibility based on your site's color mode in Plover Theme. This feature lets you show or hide specific blocks in light or dark mode—perfect for using different images or content optimized for each theme."
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:682
msgid "Global dark mode settings"
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:683
msgid "Ready to take control of dark mode across your entire site? This guide covers the global dark mode settings available through the Plover Kit plugin. You'll learn how to set the default color mode for new visitors and configure the cookie period to remember their preferences."
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:687
msgid "Advanced: Create your own toggle button"
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:688
msgid "Ready to build a custom dark mode toggle? This guide walks you through creating your own button using the Block Event Handler and visibility settings, with the exact code you'll need to make it work."
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:694
#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:697
msgid "Resources and Support"
msgstr ""

#: src/Services/DashboardServiceProvider.php:698
msgid "Looking for help with Plover Theme? This resource guide covers frequently asked questions about general setup, dark mode, customization, and the Plover Kit plugin — plus how to reach official support through forums or email."
msgstr ""

